history.text: Hi. Have you seen Toy Story?
Yes, have you?
Yes. Did you enjoy it?
Yep, I really like that Walk Disney Pictures produced it.
What do you think about the critical responses?
I do too. I also really enjoyed the music by randy Newman. I agree with the critical responses
Better yet, what do you think about Woody and Andy's relationship? Wish I had a friend like that.
I agree. I enjoyed playing with toys similar to those in the movie
They had a lot of good characters. My favorite was Rex played by Wallace Shawn.
I liked Rex as well. I think my favorite was Slinky Dog, played by Jim Varney.
Yep, the dachshund slinky toy. He was cool.
Great character for showing how each toy has it's own character like the critics said.
I agree. I was also surprised to read that Rotten Tomatoes gave it a score of 100%.
I'm not surprised. I think we need more movies like Toy Story to illustrate the freedom of imagination and creativity.
Reading the critic reviews makes me want to watch it again.
I think so as well. Cartoons nowadays do not seem as well done.
YEP. However, I'm surprised it's listed as a comedy.
I think it's safe to say that we've all had our Woody moments where we think we are more than what we are.
Yes, I did not realize that. I did not know that it was the first feature film produced by Pixar.
I agree. I think we all take on more than we can handle at times and then rely on our friends for support.

It's not until reality hits, like it did when Woody and Buzz Lightyear gets separated from Andy and his family, do we come to realize we are limited to the support of those around us. Teamwork is everything.
I didn't know baby monitors could be so versatile. The toys used them to report to other toys.
Yes, I also liked the creativity of escaping the bad situations in the movie that the characters faced.
Like using the RC

Yep. Ooh and what about how often Buzz and Woody were confronted with conflict. It was nonstop
. You see how Sid's dog interfered with their progress.
The green army men are also useful to help them spy as well.
Yes, they were faced with conflict many times and worked together to overcome it.
Yes, they were. You ever think they probably could have prepared for more toy sooner if they didn't have so many hiccups?
I would have loved to been Buzz because he had various features.
Which one would you have wanted to be?
You know how hard it must have been for the toys to pretend like they were lifeless when they encountered humans?
Yes. I enjoyed the scene where Buzz shows off his features. I think I would've wanted to be Woody.
Then we could have worked together!

I think it would've been very hard for them to put everything back in place so that the humans would not notice. 
Yes, we could have!
Sid's dog also must have been horrifying for them to encounter.
YES!
He chased them so bad. That had to be difficult for them
I also felt bad for Woody at times since he did not have as many features as Buzz.
Andy had to choose between them at times, which must have been hard.
The other toys thought differently of Woody afterwards
Of course, and then the puppy came!
I wonder what Director John Lasseter is doing now,
seems like he had a firm grip on creativity.
At least the puppy was something the both of them would have to work through together.
Yes, that is true.
Slinky Dog and Woody made quite the duo, though.
Yes, I enjoyed Slinky Dog's character.
I wish the family never stopped for gas, though.
Then Buzz wouldn't have had to hitchhike.
Yes, or moved.
Did you know that one of the executive producers was Steve Jobs?
I'm with Woody in questioning what could be worse that Buzz Lightyear after all of their issues. I think I'm satisfied with the end result
No I didn't. Totally a fun fact there.
I am satisfied with the end results as well.
What I'd give to eat at Pizza Planet. Sounds like our version of Chuck E Cheese.
Yes, I had never thought about that before
Me either
